---
import { getCollection } from "astro:content";
import PageHeader from "../components/PageHeader.astro";
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import { Image } from "astro:assets";

import cheekstand from "../assets/cheekst.png";
import choyu from "../assets/choyu.jpg";
import coldsoba from "../assets/coldsoba.jpg";
import bw from "../assets/bw.jpg";
import store from "../assets/storefront.jpg";
import "../story.css";
import StoryCard from "src/components/StoryCard.astro";

const storyEntries = await getCollection("stories");
---

<Layout title="Home">
  <div
    id="playlist-container"
    class="relative transition-all duration-1000 bg-context"
    style="min-height:100px;--context-color:rgb(97,125,138);"
  >
    <PageHeader transition:name="soba" type="soba" />
    <div class="z-10 px-6 pb-3">
      <h1
        class="font-serif text-5xl lg:text-7xl font-bold text-gray-300"
        style="color: antiquewhite;"
      >
        Our Story
      </h1>
      <h4 class="text-xl">
        We are here for the love of buckwheat, people, and its mighty story
      </h4>

      <!-- <Image src={cheekstand} alt="Lab" class="w-36" /> -->
    </div>
  </div>
  <!-- <div class="custom-pattern filter">
    <h1 class="text-5xl font-bold backdrop-brightness-50">WHY Soba?</h1>
  </div>
  <div class="custom-pattern filter">
    <h1 class="text-5xl font-bold backdrop-brightness-50">
      Buckwheat is not a grain?!
    </h1>
  </div>
  <div class="custom-pattern filter">
    <h1 class="text-5xl font-bold backdrop-brightness-50">
      Our Mission to promote regenerative business
    </h1>
     how we will help environment, bring back community and improve your health!
  </div> -->
  <div class="content">
    <div class="section">
      <h2>Why Soba?</h2>
      <p>
        At Jojosoba, we're passionate about bringing the authentic taste and
        health benefits of buckwheat soba to our community. But why soba, you
        might ask?
      </p>
      <!-- <img src="/api/placeholder/600/400" alt="Bowl of soba noodles" /> -->
      <Image src={coldsoba} alt={"SOBA"} />
      <p>
        Soba isn't just delicious; it's a nutritional powerhouse. Buckwheat, the
        main ingredient in our soba, is packed with fiber, antioxidants, and
        essential minerals. It's naturally gluten-free and has a low glycemic
        index, making it a great choice for everyone, including those with
        gluten sensitivities or those managing their blood sugar levels.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
      <h2>Buckwheat: Not Your Average Grain</h2>
      <p>
        Here's a fun fact: buckwheat isn't actually a grain at all! It's a seed
        that's used like a grain, making it a "pseudocereal." This unique plant
        has been cultivated for thousands of years, with evidence of its use
        dating back to 6000 BCE in Southeast Asia.
      </p>
      <Image src={bw} alt="Buckwheat" />

      <p>
        At Jojosoba, we celebrate this ancient food by crafting our noodles from
        100% buckwheat flour, unlike many commercial soba noodles that mix in
        wheat flour. We believe in preserving the traditional methods and
        flavors that have made soba a beloved dish for centuries.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
      <h2>Our Mission: Promoting Regenerative Business</h2>
      <p>
        We're not just here to serve great food; we're on a mission to promote
        regenerative business practices that benefit our environment, strengthen
        our community, and improve your health.
      </p>
      <ul class="flex flex-col m-2 gap-4">
        <li>
          <strong>Environment:</strong> By sourcing our buckwheat from local,
          sustainable farms, we're supporting eco-friendly agricultural
          practices that improve soil health and biodiversity.
        </li>
        <StoryCard
          story={{
            title: "Regenerating Environment",
            cover: "/assets/coldsoba.jpg",
            slug: "environment",
            tags: ["regenerative"],
          }}
        />
        <li>
          <strong>Community:</strong> We believe in the power of food to bring
          people together. Our restaurant is more than just a place to eat; it's
          a hub for cultural exchange and community building.
        </li>
        <StoryCard
          story={{
            title: "Community",
            cover: "/assets/stpt.png",
            slug: "community",
            tags: ["regenerative"],
          }}
        />
        <li>
          <strong>Health:</strong> By serving nutrient-dense, minimally
          processed foods, we're contributing to the health and wellbeing of our
          customers.
        </li>
        <StoryCard
          story={{
            title: "soba&health",
            cover: "/assets/goodwheat.png",
            slug: "health",
            tags: ["regenerative", "soba", "health"],
          }}
        />
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
      <h2>Our Unique Approach</h2>
      <p>
        At Jojosoba, we do things a little differently. We mill our own
        buckwheat flour in-house, craft our noodles by hand, and even ferment
        our own sauces. Why go through all this trouble?
      </p>
      <div class="quote">
        "We want consumers to rediscover the value of simple foods that anyone
        can make at home, using ingredients that come directly from farmers.
        We're reducing the steps of industrial processing. Milling flour,
        kneading it, cutting it into noodles, boiling them, and eating them as a
        meal is something that every household used to do without needing a
        master chef with 50 years of experience or any special qualifications."
      </div>
      <p>
        This approach not only results in fresher, more flavorful dishes, but it
        also connects us more closely to our food and its origins.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
      <h2>Join Us on This Culinary Journey</h2>
      <p>
        Whether you're a soba aficionado or new to this delightful noodle, we
        invite you to experience the Jojosoba difference. Come taste the rich
        history and bright future of buckwheat soba, served with a side of
        community and sustainability.
      </p>
      <Image src={store} alt="store front" />
    </div>
  </div>
